docs.snippet: It is perfectly evident that President McKINLEY, in sketching out his annual message to Congress, ought not to omit to provide a paragraph somewhere to counteract the distrust of our intentions that is being cultivated by the anti-imperialist press...
docs.lead_paragraph: It is perfectly evident that President McKINLEY, in sketching out his annual message to Congress, ought not to omit to provide a paragraph somewhere to counteract the distrust of our intentions that is being cultivated by the anti-imperialist press in those South American republics that have in large part adopted Constitutions resembling our own and have for many years entertained a feeling of fellow-republicanism toward the United States.
